\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4919515 {\*\atrfstart 419667519}The wo
man gave a frightened look into his face and ran a few steps; then she stopped and came timidly back and addressed the strangers in an unknown tongue. Among the Indian crew there were several dialects spoken, but no one in the party was able to understand
 
a word she uttered. Nidiver describes her as a magnificent specimen of womanhood, between forty and fifty years old, erect, with well-formed neck and limbs and unwrinkled face. She wore a tunic-shaped garment made of birds' plumage low in the neck, sleeve
less and reaching to the ankle----a dress similar to the  one found in the tree.
\par 
\par The woman made no objection to leaving the island, and Captain Nidiver took her to his own home. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\fs16\insrsid12083645 {\*\atrfend 419667519}{\*\atnid SS}{\*\atnauthor Sara Schwebel}\chatn 
{\*\annotation{\*\atnref 419667519}{\*\atndate 1194480530}\ltrpar \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\ql \li0\ri0\sa160\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\fs16\insrsid12083645 \chatn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12083645 Indian Queen}}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4919515 
Her coming created a sensation all along the California coast. Efforts were made by the Franciscan fathers to learn her story, but although they had a hundred dialects at their command, they could not make themselves understood{\*\atrfstart 419667520}
. The gentleness, modesty and sweetness of the woman from the sea were so foreign to the idea of savage nature, that many believed she was not an Indian, but a woman of distinction cast away on San Nicolas by shipwreck. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\fs16\insrsid12083645 {\*\atrfend 419667520}{\*\atnid SS}{\*\atnauthor Sara Schwebel}\chatn {\*\annotation{\*\atnref 419667520}{\*\atndate 1194480530}\ltrpar \pard\plain \ltrpar
