\par 
\par The mystery was never solved. {\*\atrfstart 419667522}Civilization did not agree with the wild woman of the Pacific. She missed the outdoor life of her island camp. In a few weeks she began to droop and became so weak that she had to be carried about in 
a chair. One morning, while dozing in the sunshine on the veranda, she fell from the chair and remained insensible for hours. Mrs. Nidiver summoned the Mission priest. He baptized the unknown woman as "Juana Marie" and administered the last rite. As she b
reathed her last the sign of the cross was pressed to her cold brow.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\fs16\insrsid12083645 {\*\atrfend 419667522}{\*\atnid SS}{\*\atnauthor Sara Schwebel}\chatn {\*\annotation{\*\atnref 419667522}
